<br>
I just wanted to make this thread - I know a bunch of enchanters on Veeshan who happen to have TD3 and Command of Druzzil.<br>
<br>
The point is, most see this as a dream; they are using it as long as they can, milking it for what it's worth ( a bit like manaburn, but on a lower scale ), but they are fulling expecting the nerf bat to come down on them.<br>
<br>
I think that enchanters that say it's dangerous soloing in Hohonora with this charm are being unrealistic in the extreme... We all know with Rune of Zebuxxoruk and the aa rune, risk is close to 0. Even if perchance you die, you make up for lost experience in maybe four mobs.<br>
<br>
I am glad for my enchanter friends who happen to have this ability, and who have fun soloing or contributing huge DPS to groups/raids. I think that all the mages who get their panties in a bunch and call for nerf, should remember how we feel when we read about our 'grossly overpowered pets' on the monk boards.<br>
<br>
You don't need to call for it - it's going to happen. Not because the other classes cry, but simply because SoE, slow and somewhat dimwitted as they may seem, are far from oblivious. It took a manaburn crew to kill Wuoshi, and this single person did it.<br>
<br>
How long do you think it will last? Until now, I hope all the enchanters have fun with that ability. I must admit it rocks, and that I am looking forward to using my charm on the elemental planes/Bastion of Thunder, if I ever get it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kalahadbb>KalahadBB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 182<br> <font color=#333333>(12/4/02 8:05:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8057.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: About Charm</span><hr size=1> Long as they leave the mage charm alone, do what they want to enchanters =(. <p>Arch Convoker Kalahad<br>
