As i said several times before, the difference between monks calling mage pets overpowered, and me calling charm overpowered, is the fact that mage pets really are not overpowered but charm is. <br>
<br>
Any anger a mage feels over reading their pets being called overpowered, is out of knowing its not true. Well at least thats why i get angry when people call our new pets overpowered. Our pets are <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>finally</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> where they should be, and people are saying thats unfair? <br>
<br>
If i felt mage pets were overpowered, i <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>would</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> aknowledge it. They arent. Monks are compairing themselves to the positive atributes of all of our pets - the mitigation of the air pet, and the damage of a backstabbing nuking water pet. What they fail to realize is you cant have both at once.<br>
<br>
Mage pets do as much damage as any other classes pet. Yes, i parsed many raid logs and find on average the beastlord pet will do more melee damage than the water pet, if the water pet cant backstab. This is just using their first level pet too, i assume their other 60+ pets will do even more damage. <br>
Im sure the warder also tanks better than the water pet too, or at least almost as well.<br>
<br>
The air pet doesnt out tank monks. Like i said before, a monk guildie decided to attack my pet when ld and it wasnt even a contest. The pet couldnt even hit him. <br>
Even if it were true that mage pets and pets in general could out tank monks, all that means is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>monks</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> are broken. It does not mean that pets are, since pets are in line with every other class.<br>
<br>
Whereas, enchanters <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>are</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> soloing hoh, they <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>are</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> doing multiple rogues, and multiple mages worth of damage for a nominal risk, while also having the best abilities to avoid and mitigate damage, as well as support other classes through buffs.<br>
<br>
Sorry, but being the best at damage avoidance, having some of the best supportive spells, as well as many times the best abilities in damage dealing is a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>god class</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. God classes should not exist as they comprimise game integrity. Thats how i feel about this issue, and whenever the topic comes up i will say how i feel. :/<br>
<br>
The way i look at it, if you are an enchanter who charms, and feel bad about people saying what you are doing is overpowered, you are being dishonest with yourself, with me, or are just generally ignorant of what other classes are capable of so you dont realize how overpowered that is relative to others. <br>
<br>
I dont think charm should be removed from this game at all, its a cool ability, i just think it needs to be seriously rebalanced. So even if me saying that makes someone feel bad, sorry but i feel it is the truth. <br>
<br>
If i were a member of the enchanter community, i wouldnt take such a counter productive stance of denying the power of charm that most seem to favor. That is not effective, because eventually the truth will come out on a large scale denial will no longer be an effective tactic. <br>
Once that happens, verant <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>will</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> rebalance it. So the question enchanters should be asking themselves is, do they want to be rebalanced like monks and avoidance was, or do they want to be rebalanced like mages and mod rod 2 was?<br>
<br>
The reason monks are broken now, is because they never really expressed as a comunity how they feel their class should be. They just sat back, enjoyed doing almost as much damage as rogues while tanking better than warriors, assuming nothing would happen. So, verant &quot;rebalanced&quot; them, without knowing the desires of the class. What verant did to the monk class, was basically remove the overpowered element, which in doing so made monks an incomplete class, without offering compensitory abilities to make them balanced. Thats because verant did not know where monks wanted to be as a class, since monks never admited there was a problem.<br>
<br>
Whereas,  mages had always expressed as a community what they feel their class should be. Mages wanted to be a damage dealing class with minor supportive and utility abilities. After verant removed the arguably overpowered mod rod 2, we were compensated with increased offense, as per our wishes.<br>
<br>
If i were an enchanter, i would start thinking of creative solutions to making charm a useful ability, without it being an overpowered ability, and vocalizing these opinions.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=noonievioletskies>NoonieVioletskies</A> at: 12/4/02 12:39:16 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solovey>Solovey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 314<br> <font color=#333333>(12/4/02 12:38:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8057.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://myweb.ecomplanet.com/COLL8955/mystorage/fireelemental.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: About Charm</span><hr size=1> Frankly I am happy for the chanters <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , Charm is really really usefull now.<br>
<br>
However I do agree with noonie 100% on the Issue of the misconception of our pets.<br>
<br>
Monks are rolling all our pets up into one super pet, Let me decribe the pet monks &quot;think we have&quot;<br>
<br>
Magme ellemental surrounded by steam!!<br>
<br>
