Please PLEASE understand, The pet's you think of are only in your imagination. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dukeofthesky>Duke of the sky</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 132<br> <font color=#333333>(12/4/02 1:13:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8057.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   .</span><hr size=1> I didn't say our pet was overpowered - I was just making a comparison, I know very well the pet monks credit us for doesn't exist ( hey, I wish it did <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ).<br>
<br>
What I am saying is that a lot of mages are screaming bloody murders because of enchanters with CoD and TD3. My friend admits that this is way overpowered; he's not going to shout it, he's not going to write posts about it, but he doesn't deny it when people do say it.<br>
<br>
Put it this way - change enchanter with mage, and charm with double bolt. Would you go around shouting for a nerf or bragging about it? No. Some of us did, and look what happened. I mean, it took them more than two years... Had there not been so many posts in a short period of time over here, we probably would still have them, because we had been silent.<br>
<br>
Yes, I am aware this is on a much larger scale than double bolts; enchanters who try to defend with 'there is danger' or ( my favorite ) 'It takes lots of aa points' are being hypocrits. We all know experience is easy to come by. Especially in PoP, where every damn group needs a slower, and where enchanters have never looked as good.<br>
<br>
Enchanter soloes Wuoshi - do you think that goes unnoticed? I mean, enchanters soloing in PoP goes unnoticed; they don't post pics of that, and they don't go around bragging about it. But, when you solo a dragon... Well, you know what's going to happen.<br>
<br>
What I'm saying is only - let them enjoy it. I mean, this isn't Manaburn where a bunch of greedy folks get together and basically put guilds that are starting to develop out of mobs to kill. It doesn't hurt anyone ( so far ). Is it a fair advantage? No. Neither were mod rods, double bolts, monks tanking the way they did or that cleric got their best spell at 39 ( and still do ).<br>
<br>
I'm just happy to see enchanters have fun. I wish they all were like my friend, that is, aware this is not going to be permanent; if they will be disappointed when it ends, then... Well, then they are fools, because no one can expect such a permanent advantage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ylaine76>Ylaine76</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1172<br> <font color=#333333>(12/4/02 1:38:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8057.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .</span><hr size=1> Here is how I see it, charm is fine in groups and fine in raids.. However I don't see how people think its *okay* solo because chanters DONT want to group and ya know what? Chanters are a much needed class and it pisses a lot of people off that we gotta sit LFG cause we have no CCer or slower while the chanter solos close to 5x or 10x faster than *every* other class, im sorry but thats very imbalanced whether or not charm is &quot;fun&quot;.  VI has nerfed soloing for much less of reasons before and this is hypocritical that they let a class solo this well, let it be chanters, druids (They're doing the same thing), necros, wizards or mages <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/YlaineEQ/fullsize/cheersig2.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
